16 SECTION 2. IC 35-35-3-5 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
17 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) As a part of the
ES 9—LS 6094/DI 149

2
1 recommendation submitted to the court, the prosecuting attorney must
2 certify that he the prosecuting attorney has offered to show the
3 proposed recommendation to the victims of the felony, if any, and that
4 they have been offered an opportunity to present their opinion of the
5 recommendation to the prosecuting attorney and the court.
6 (b) A victim present at sentencing in a felony or misdemeanor case
7 shall be advised by the court of a victim's right to make a statement
8 concerning the crime and the sentence. The court shall also offer the
9 victim, if present, an opportunity to make a statement concerning the
10 crime and the sentence. If unable to attend the hearing, the victim may
11 mail a written statement to the court, which must be included in the
12 presentence report made with respect to the defendant.
13 (c) However, this section gives no additional rights to the defendant.
14 Failure to comply gives no grounds for postconviction relief.
15 (d) The defendant shall be present in the courtroom while a
16 victim makes a statement concerning the crime and the sentence
17 under this section, unless the defendant presents a safety risk or
18 causes a significant disruption.
19 (e) If a defendant fails to appear at the sentencing hearing, and
20 is later taken into custody, the sentencing court shall, upon motion
21 by the prosecuting attorney, hold a hearing at which a victim has
22 the right to make a statement in the presence of the defendant
23 concerning the crime and the sentence, unless the defendant
24 presents a safety risk or causes a significant disruption.
25 (f) Subsection (d) does not prohibit a court from sentencing a
26 defendant who is absent from the courtroom.
27 SECTION 3. IC 35-38-1-12 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
28 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 12. (a) Before imposing
29 sentence, the court shall:
30 (1) advise the defendant or his the defendant's counsel and the
31 prosecuting attorney of the factual contents and conclusions of the
32 presentence investigation; or
33 (2) provide the defendant or his the defendant's counsel and the
34 prosecuting attorney with a copy of the presentence report.
35 The court also shall offer the victim, if present, an opportunity to make
36 a statement concerning the crime and the sentence. Except as
37 provided in subsection (c), the defendant shall be present in the
38 courtroom while a victim makes a statement concerning the crime
39 and the sentence under this subsection, unless the defendant
40 presents a safety risk or causes a significant disruption.
41 (b) The sources of confidential information need not be disclosed.
42 The court shall furnish the factual contents of the presentence
